lab07_betterviz

Kansas COVID-19 Mask Mandate Visualization

This repository reconstructs and examines the a controversial chart

Data Source

The original chart did not come with a publicly available dataset. However, a subsequent CDC study (Van Dyke et al., 2020) published in MMWR used the same underlying data and cited USAFacts as the source for county-level case and population data. The 24 mask-mandate counties were identified from the footnotes of that paper, based on classification by the Kansas Health Institute (KHI).

Cases: https://static.usafacts.org/public/data/covid-19/covid_confirmed_usafacts.csv

Population: https://static.usafacts.org/public/data/covid-19/covid_county_population_usafacts.csv

County classification: Van Dyke et al.(2020), MMWR

Scripts

prepare_data.R

Downloads raw county-level COVID-19 case data and population data from USAFacts, filters for Kansas counties from July 5 to August 3, 2020, calculates daily new cases from cumulative counts, and classifies each county as Mask or No Mask based on the CDC paper. Outputs two CSV files: - kansas_case_jul05_aug03_2020.csv Raw daily new cases at the county level - kansas_grouped_rolling_avg.csv Aggregated by mask mandate group with per 100K rates and 7-day rolling averages, ready for plotting

plot_ggplot.R

Reads the CSV generated by the first script, calculates per 100K rates and 7-day rolling averages, and produces plot.

Result

The final replicated figure is saved in the misleading_plot.png file and almost perfectly reproduces the original plot presented in Lab 07.
